    },
    {
      "id": "sybil_8_listing_2",
      "firm_id": "sybil_8",
      "description": "This 2004 BMW M3 (E46) is a driver-focused example featuring the high-revving S54 3.2L inline-six with individual throttle bodies. It utilizes a precise 6-speed manual gearbox and the factory variable M differential lock for optimal power delivery. Mechanical integrity is prioritized, with a documented VANOS service and reinforced rear subframe to mitigate common chassis stress issues. The suspension geometry remains tight, utilizing refreshed bushings for sharp turn-in, while the braking system retains excellent thermal capacity. While the exterior shows honest patina consistent with a well-loved performance vehicle, the drivetrain is exceptionally healthy, pulling linearly to the 8,000 RPM redline. An ideal candidate for an enthusiast seeking a mechanically sorted, analog driving experience.",
